tes the key aims and objectives of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">BenX</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">.  </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The group will have a Chair and Vice </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Chair – these roles will be reviewed on an annual basis (April of each year).</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Local authority members are currently; </span></li><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 66.2pt; padding-left:5.8pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Cambridge City Council, Colchester Borough Council, Ipswich Borough Council/ </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Babergh</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> District Council/ Mid Suffolk District Council (shar</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ed service), City of Lincoln Council/ North </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Kesteven</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> District Council (shared service), Hertsmere Borough Council, Luton Borough Council, North Hertfordshire District Council, Oxford City Council, St Albans City &amp; District Council, Three Rivers District Co</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">uncil/ Watford Borough Council (shared service), and Welwyn Hatfield Borough Council. </span></li></ul></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The group will aim to meet on a quarterly basis (normally in the last week of the month following the end of a financial quarter) – as well as for any ‘ad hoc’ meetings</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> when required – i.e. including meetings with DWP.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Each participating local authority will aim to provide representation at each meeting, and will host meetings on a rota basis (in alphabetical order of local authority).</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">These Terms of Reference will be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">reviewed annually (in April), or as and when required.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">BenX</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline"> will</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Act as a “think tank”/lobby group;</span></li></ul></ul></ul></ul></ul></ul></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 67.5pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-13.5pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Act as a discussion forum regarding new Housing Benefit/ Council Tax Support, Council Tax, NNDR (or related) legislation and policy, to assist in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">successful implementation of new procedures;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 67.5pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-13.5pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Make recommendations and lobby for changes to Housing Benefit/ Council Tax Support, Council Tax and NNDR policy, or related areas, to improve service delivery;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 67.5pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-13.5pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ct as a consultative working-group for other agenc</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ies (for example, Department for Work and Pensions, DCLG), to assist in changes to legislation, policy and procedures.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Actively pursue efficiencies and achieve Value For Money;</span></li></ul></ul></ul></ul></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">To formulate and develop best practice.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Investigate use of new systems and pro</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">cesses.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Review and analyse key performance measures:</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">To agree key performance measures relating to Benefits, Revenues and customer service – which </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">BenX</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> member authorities will monitor, benchmark and manage.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">L</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">andlords (private rented sector a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">nd Registered Social Landlords):</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">erms of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">private sector landlords, as Local Housing Allowance (LHA) has been in place for several years the issue of direct payment is relatively well established – although there are still instances of tenants not paying their Housing Benefit (HB) over to their la</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ndlords.  Local authorities are experience</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in, and have the local knowledge to make ‘vulnerability’ decisions relating to direct payment and have done this successfully for a number of years.  Customers being paid Universal Credit (UC) monthly in arrears will cause an issue to many claimants in th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e first instance and support and financial </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">advice</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> would need to be provided to assist, in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">particularly</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, vulnerable individuals and groups.  </span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Similar issues </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">will apply for RSLs, although the added factor of direct payment would be new, and would cause issue</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s for RSLs in terms of increased rent arrears, recovery costs and potential for increased evictions due to non-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">payment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> of rent.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In all cases, local authorities would be well placed and have the skills and local knowledge to provide the support needed.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">L</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">oc</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">al authorities (including availability of Discretionary Housing Payments (DHPs))</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">UC provides a number of key challenges for local authorities:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Reduction in local empowerment/ control – e.g. if a customer comes into the HB office late on a Friday afternoon and is about to be evicted, with the right information the HB office can ‘fast-track’ a case and make a payment by CHAPS to prevent an eviction</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  Concern this would be lost under UC resulting in evictions, increased potential for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">dissatisfied</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> customers</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Loss of local knowledge/ knowledge of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">individual</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> clients/ groups</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Potentially a reduction in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">funding</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> but with at least the same (if not more) need to support customers</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Digital inclusion – to continue and improve strategies</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">DHPs – any reduction in funding will have an impact as these monies are vital in terms of providing short-term support to those in ne</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ed</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Increased rent arrears and recovery costs for local authority tenants</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">New partnerships to be established to help customers find employment.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">laimants, particularly those in vulnerable groups (such as people with disabilities and families with children)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">, and those in supported and temporary accommodation.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Over many years local authorities have established well run working relationships with local housing providers and vulnerable groups.  Named contacts in HB offices </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">assist to make these run effectively. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> These relationships </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">are vital</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to ensure that customers receive the information, help and support they need.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In summary, although wholly </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">recognising</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the need for the Benefits system to be simplified, inclusion of housing costs in UC is a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">significant</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> issue due to local variances, knowledge and expertise, established relationships with housing providers and vulnerable groups, and potential for increasing homelessness (in turn increasing the costs of housing customers in temporary accommodation).  Local</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> authorities are well placed to overcome such issues.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">27 September 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>